Description. General features —Idiosoma roundish; frontal platelets slightly shorter than shoulder platelets (shoulder/frontal platelets L ratio 1.05–1.07 ); frontal margin medially pointed, between anterolaterally orientated apodemes (
Fig. 34 A
); Cxgl- 4 located far anteriorly, near tip of Cx-I; gnathosomal bay deep U-shaped, proximally wide box-shaped; posterior suture line of Cx-IV strongly extending posteriorly beyond posterior margin of genital field, laterally curved; excretory pore and Vgl- 2 away from the line of primary sclerotization, Vgl- 2 posterior to excretory pore; gnathosoma nearly triangular in lateral view, with short, cone-shaped rostrum (
Fig. 34 G
); P- 2 longer than P- 4 , P- 2 ventral margin straight or slightly concave, bearing long and slender ventral seta located away from distal edge, P- 3 ventral margin concave, P- 4 bowed, ventral margin with setae-bearing protrusion in the centre of the segment (
Figs. 34 D–E
,
35 B
). Male: medial margin of Cx-II/III relatively short; genital field subrectangular. Female: genital field pentagonal.

